{
  "texts": [
    "It can treat both regular and irreugular time-series data by a deformation of the standard Wiener process.TimeGAN [6] uses a GAN architecture to generate timeseries.",
    "First, it trains an encoder and decoder, which transform a time-series sample x 1:N into latent vectors h 1:N and recover them by using a recurrent neural network (RNN).",
    "Next, it trains a generator and discriminator pair on latent space, by minimizing the discrepancy between an estimated and true distribution, i.e.",
    "p(x n |x 1:n-1) and p(x n |x 1:n-1).",
    "Since it uses an RNN-based encoder, it can efficiently learn the conditional likelihood p(x n |x 1:n-1) by treating it as p(h n |h n-1), since h n ∼ x 1:n under the regime of RNNs."
  ]
}